{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:28:11.319Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Type hints annotate Python code with expected types for parameters, return values, and variables. They do not change runtime behavior by default, but they document agent tool contracts, enable static analysis, and improve IDE support when building LLM clients, orchestrators, and tool registries."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is"}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Python type hints: anatomy of a typed function, common annotation categories, and type check lifecycle"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A "}, {"type": "text", "text": "type hint", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a static annotation describing the intended type of a value. Python stores hints in "}, {"type": "text", "text": "__annotations__", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " but does not enforce them at runtime unless you add a separate validator (mypy, pyright, Pydantic)."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "def search(query: str, top_k: int = 5) -> list[str]:\n    return retriever.search(query, limit=top_k)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why it matters"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Agent code passes structured data between prompts, parsers, tools, and persistence. Hints make those shapes explicit: a message list is "}, {"type": "text", "text": "list[dict[str, str]]", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", a tool returns "}, {"type": "text", "text": "dict[str, Any]", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", a client method returns "}, {"type": "text", "text": "str", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ". Static checkers catch mismatches before deployment; IDEs autocomplete fields and flag wrong argument types."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefits"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Documentation", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 signatures describe tool and client contracts"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Early error detection", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 mypy/pyright find type bugs in CI"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "IDE intelligence", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 autocomplete and inline errors while authoring agent code"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Schema alignment", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 hints mirror JSON tool schemas for LLM function calling"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-offs"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Not runtime validation", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 wrong types still pass at runtime without Pydantic"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Annotation overhead", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 complex generics add syntax cost"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradual adoption", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 mixed typed/untyped codebases need discipline at boundaries"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How it works"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Function and variable annotations"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from typing import Any\n\nmessages: list[dict[str, str]] = []\ntemperature: float = 0.7\n\ndef complete(messages: list[dict[str, str]], model: str) -> str:\n    ...\n\ndef parse_tool_output(raw: str) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    ..."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Built-in generic syntax (Python 3.9+)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Prefer built-in collections over typing.List/Dict in new code\nnames: list[str] = [\"search\", \"code\"]\nconfig: dict[str, int | str] = {\"max_tokens\": 4096, \"model\": \"gpt-4o\"}\n\n# Union with | (Python 3.10+)\ndef find(id: str) -> dict | None:\n    ..."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "typing module essentials"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from typing import Any, Callable\n\n# Callable for tool functions\nToolFn = Callable[..., dict[str, Any]]\n\nREGISTRY: dict[str, ToolFn] = {\n    \"search\": search_docs,\n}"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to use it"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Annotate", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " all public tool functions, client methods, and agent entry points"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Annotate", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " module-level config and state with clear types"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Skip", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " hints on trivial local variables when type is obvious \u2014 focus on boundaries"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How to implement"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "class LLMClient:\n    def __init__(self, api_key: str, base_url: str) -> None:\n        self.api_key = api_key\n        self.base_url = base_url\n\n    def chat(\n        self,\n        messages: list[dict[str, str]],\n        *,\n        temperature: float = 0.7,\n        max_tokens: int = 1024,\n    ) -> str:\n        ..."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Examples"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Literal for fixed string sets (roles, finish reasons)\nfrom typing import Literal\n\nRole = Literal[\"system\", \"user\", \"assistant\", \"tool\"]\n\ndef append_message(messages: list[dict], role: Role, content: str) -> None:\n    messages.append({\"role\": role, \"content\": content})"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Real-world example"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A typed tool module exports functions whose signatures match OpenAI-style JSON schemas \u2014 reviewers and static tools verify argument types align:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "def search_docs(query: str, top_k: int = 5) -> list[str]:\n    \"\"\"Return document IDs matching query.\"\"\"\n    ...\n\ndef run_python(code: str, timeout: float = 30.0) -> dict[str, str]:\n    \"\"\"Execute code in sandbox; return stdout/stderr.\"\"\"\n    ..."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common mistakes"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Treating hints as validation", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 runtime still accepts wrong types"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Using Any everywhere", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 defeats the purpose at agent boundaries"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Outdated typing imports", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 "}, {"type": "text", "text": "from typing import List", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " when "}, {"type": "text", "text": "list[str]", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " suffices in 3.9+"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Missing return on all paths", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 mypy flags inconsistent returns in tool wrappers"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best practices"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Type public APIs first; expand inward"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Run mypy or pyright in CI on agent packages"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Match hint types to tool JSON schema field types"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use "}, {"type": "text", "text": "from __future__ import annotations", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for forward references in older patterns"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Tooling and ecosystem"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "mypy", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 widely used static checker"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "pyright", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " / "}, {"type": "text", "text": "Pylance", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 fast checking in VS Code/Cursor"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Type hints are "}, {"type": "text", "text": "labels on shipping boxes", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 they tell handlers what should be inside without opening every box at runtime. Enforcement happens at the warehouse gate (static checker) or with a scanner (Pydantic), not automatically when Python runs the code."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hints document intent; they do not validate at runtime by default"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Annotate agent tools, clients, and message structures first"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use modern syntax: list[str], dict[str, int], str | None"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Integrate a static checker in CI for agent packages"}]}]}]}]}}